---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import GeneratorShell from '../../components/GeneratorShell.astro';

const title = 'Free Mission Statement Generator | Genfy';
const description = 'Generate a clear, short, focused mission statement. Ready for your website, pitch deck, brand brief or internal team document.';

const faqSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'FAQPage',
  mainEntity: [
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How long should a mission statement be?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Between 12 and 25 words. One sentence the whole team can repeat from memory. If it needs a paragraph, it is not a mission — it is a pitch.' } },
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Difference between mission and vision?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Mission is what you do today and for whom. Vision is where you want to be in 5-10 years. Mission drives the day; vision drives the strategy.' } },
    { '@type': 'Question', name: 'Useful for small companies?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Especially. A small company with a clear mission filters decisions better, hires more sharply and communicates with less effort. One of the few assets that costs no money.' } },
  ],
};
---
<Layout title={title} description={description} lang="en" schema={faqSchema} withSidebar={true}>
  <GeneratorShell lang="en" tag="Branding" title="Mission Statement Generator"
    intro="Drop in what you do, for whom, and how. Genfy structures your mission into a clear, short, memorable sentence the team can recite by heart.">

    <div slot="tool" class="ms">
      <label for="ms-what">What you do (verb + product)</label>
      <input id="ms-what" type="text" placeholder="We help freelancers invoice..." value="We help freelancers invoice" />

      <label for="ms-who" style="margin-top:1rem">For whom?</label>
      <input id="ms-who" type="text" placeholder="small businesses, freelancers..." value="freelancers in the US" />

      <label for="ms-how" style="margin-top:1rem">How? (what makes you different)</label>
      <input id="ms-how" type="text" placeholder="with fewer clicks, no paperwork..." value="in under a minute, without an accountant" />

      <button id="ms-gen" class="btn btn-primary" type="button" style="margin-top:1rem">Generate 6 versions</button>

      <div id="ms-out" class="ms-out"></div>
    </div>

    <div slot="content">
      <h2>What a mission statement is and why it matters</h2>
      <p>
        A mission is the sentence that answers, in fewer than 25 words, what your company does, for whom, and why. It's not marketing; it's operations. A good mission filters product decisions ("does this move us closer or farther?"), filters hiring ("does this person connect with this?"), and filters customers ("are we selling to the people we want to?").
      </p>
      <p>
        Great missions have three components: a concrete action (a verb in the present), a specific audience (not "everyone" but a real segment), and a differential promise (what you do better or differently). Miss any one and what you have is a slogan, not a mission.
      </p>

      <h2>Anatomy of missions that work</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Stripe:</strong> "Increase the GDP of the internet." Ambitious, brief, actionable.</li>
        <li><strong>Patagonia:</strong> "We're in business to save our home planet." Clear, filters every decision.</li>
        <li><strong>Notion:</strong> "Make software toolmaking ubiquitous, so anyone can build their own tools." Focused and actionable.</li>
        <li><strong>Tesla:</strong> "Accelerate the world's transition to sustainable energy." Verb-led, specific mechanism.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        None of them talk about "being leaders in their space" or "quality and excellence". That's empty language. Missions that work are verbs.
      </p>

      <h2>The practical formula in three blocks</h2>
      <p>If you have to write it in 10 minutes, use this structure:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Verb + object:</strong> "We help freelancers invoice."</li>
        <li><strong>For whom (specific):</strong> "...freelancers in the US..."</li>
        <li><strong>How (differential):</strong> "...in under a minute, without an accountant."</li>
      </ol>
      <p>
        Result: "We help freelancers in the US invoice in under a minute, without an accountant." 16 words. Three components covered, repeatable from memory.
      </p>

      <h2>Mistakes that empty out a mission</h2>
      <p>
        The most frequent: empty adjectives. "We deliver superior quality products with a focus on innovation and customer satisfaction." Any company in the world could sign that. If swapping the subject still works, it's not yours.
      </p>
      <p>
        Others: stacking objectives ("we help companies, freelancers and students..." loses focus), internal jargon the customer doesn't speak, being so ambitious it stops being actionable ("change the world"), or copying a competitor's mission with two words swapped.
      </p>

      <h2>Mission vs. vision vs. values</h2>
      <p>These three get blurred. Worth separating:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Mission:</strong> what you do today, for whom, how. Present tense.</li>
        <li><strong>Vision:</strong> where you'll be in 5-10 years. Future tense.</li>
        <li><strong>Values:</strong> how the team behaves on the way. Culture.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Mission drives the day and tactical decisions. Vision drives the long term and strategy. Values filter people. The three should fit on one A4 page with breathing room.
      </p>

      <h2>How to test your mission before adopting it</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Have every team member recite it from memory 24 hours later.</li>
        <li>Ask an outsider to read it and tell you what company they imagine.</li>
        <li>Test it on a real decision: does this new feature move us closer or farther?</li>
        <li>Confirm a competitor couldn't sign it without changing anything.</li>
        <li>Check it has no empty adjectives: quality, innovation, excellence, leading.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div slot="faq">
      <details><summary>How long should it be?</summary><p>12-25 words. One sentence the team can recite from memory.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Mission vs. vision?</summary><p>Mission: today. Vision: 5-10 years out. Mission drives the day; vision drives strategy.</p></details>
      <details><summary>Useful for small companies?</summary><p>Especially. It filters decisions, hires and customers with less effort.</p></details>
      <details><summary>How often to revisit it?</summary><p>Every 2-3 years or after a major pivot. Changing it every 6 months means it was marketing, not mission.</p></details>
    </div>
  </GeneratorShell>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ms-out { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.5rem; margin-top: 1.25rem; }
  .ms-item { padding: 0.875rem 1.125rem; background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: var(--radius-sm); cursor: pointer; transition: border-color 0.1s; line-height: 1.5; }
  .ms-item:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }
</style>

<script>
  const TPL = [
    '{what} for {who} {how}.',
    'We exist to {whatLow} for {who}, {how}.',
    'Our mission: {whatLow} for {who}, {how}.',
    '{what} for {who}. {How}.',
    'We build so {who} can {whatVerb}, {how}.',
    'We make sure {who} can {whatVerb} {how}.',
  ];

  const what = document.getElementById('ms-what') as HTMLInputElement;
  const who = document.getElementById('ms-who') as HTMLInputElement;
  const how = document.getElementById('ms-how') as HTMLInputElement;
  const gen = document.getElementById('ms-gen') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const out = document.getElementById('ms-out')!;

  function generate() {
    const W = what.value.trim() || 'We help businesses grow';
    const wLow = W.charAt(0).toLowerCase() + W.slice(1);
    const wVerb = wLow.replace(/^we\s+/, '');
    const wh = who.value.trim() || 'small businesses';
    const h = how.value.trim() || 'without friction';
    const H = h.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + h.slice(1);
    out.innerHTML = '';
    TPL.forEach(t => {
      const s = t.replace(/\{what\}/g, W).replace(/\{whatLow\}/g, wLow).replace(/\{whatVerb\}/g, wVerb).replace(/\{who\}/g, wh).replace(/\{how\}/g, h).replace(/\{How\}/g, H);
      const el = document.createElement('div');
      el.className = 'ms-item';
      el.textContent = s;
      el.title = 'Click to copy';
      el.addEventListener('click', () => { navigator.clipboard.writeText(s); el.textContent = '✓ ' + s; setTimeout(() => el.textContent = s, 800); });
      out.appendChild(el);
    });
  }
  gen.addEventListener('click', generate);
  generate();
</script>
